{"title_page": "Gulshan Town", "text_new": "{{Use Pakistani English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->| name                            = Gulshan Town\n| native_name                     = <br/>{{Nastaliq|\u06af\u0644\u0634\u0646 \u0679\u0627\u0624\u0646}}\n| settlement_type                 = [[Towns in Karachi|Constituent Town of Karachi]]\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->| image_skyline                   = \n| image_caption                   = Millennium Mall, Askari Chowrangi\n| image_flag                      = \n| image_seal                      = \n| image_map                       = GulshanTown Karachi.PNG\n| map_caption                     = Gulshan Town was divided into 13 Union Councils\n<!-- Location ------------------>| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Pakistan]]\n| subdivision_type1               = Province\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Sindh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = City District\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Karachi]]\n| parts_type                      = Union Councils\n| parts_style                     = para\n| parts                           = 13\n| p1                              = [[Civic Centre (Karachi)|Civic Centre]]\n| p2                              = [[Delhi Mercantile Society]]\n| p3                              = [[Essa Nagri]]\n| p4                              = [[Gillani Railway Station]]\n| p5                              = [[Gulshan-e-Iqbal I]]\n| p6                              = [[Gulshan-e-Iqbal II]]\n| p7                              = [[Gulzar-e-Hijri]]\n| p8                              = [[Jamali Colony]]\n| p9                              = [[Metroville Colony]]\n| p10                             = [[Pehlwan Goth]]\n| p11                             = [[Pir Ilahi Buksh Colony|P.I.B. Colony]]\n| p12                             = [[Safooran Goth]]\n| p13                             = [[Shanti Nagar]]\n<!-- Politics ----------------->| government_footnotes            = \n| government_type                 = Town Council\n| leader_title                    = Town Nazim\n| leader_name                     = Muhammad Wasay Jalil\n| leader_title1                   = Naib Nazim\n| leader_name1                    = Shoib Akhtar\n| leader_title2                   = Municipal Officer\n| leader_name2                    = Muhammad Shafiqur Rehman\n| established_title               = Established\n| established_date                = 14 August 2001\n<!-- Area    --------------------->| area_magnitude                  = 1 E+6\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| area_total_sq_mi                = <!-- Elevation -------------------------->\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = <!-- Population   ----------------------->\n| population_as_of                = 1998\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = 646,662\n<!-- General information  --------------->| timezone                        = \n| utc_offset                      = \n| timezone_DST                    = \n| utc_offset_DST                  = \n| latd                            = \n| latm                            = \n| lats                            = \n| latNS                           = \n| longd                           = \n| longm                           = \n| longs                           = \n| longEW                          = <!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n| postal_code_type                = <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| website                         = [http://125.209.91.254/CDGK/LinkClick.aspx?link=200&tabid=72 Gulshan Town Page]\n| blank_name                      = Office Location\n| blank_info                      = Plot#14, Scheme 24, Adjacent Civic Center, University Road Karachi\n| blank1_name                     = E-mail\n| blank1_info                     = nazim@tmagulshan.com\n| blank2_name                     = Contact\n| blank2_info                     = (021) 99230355-9 & (021) 99231363\n| footnotes                       = <center>[http://www.tmagulshan.com/ TMA Gulshan website]</center>\n| official_name                   = \n| extinct_title                   = Disbanded\n| extinct_date                    = 2011\n}}{{About|the defunct administrative unit that existed between 2001 and 2011|the [[Karachi]] suburb|Gulshan-e-Iqbal}}\n'''Gulshan Town''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u06af\u0644\u0634\u0646 \u0679\u0627\u0624\u0646}}}}) was a [[Towns in Karachi|Karachi borough]] in the northeastern part of [[Karachi]]. Gulshan Town was formed in 2001 as part of [https://web.archive.org/web/20081013065059/http://www.nrb.gov.pk/city_district/index.html The Local Government Ordinance 2001], and was subdivided into 11 [[Union councils of Pakistan|Union Councils]]. The Town system was disbanded in 2011,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewstribe.com/2011/07/11/karachi%e2%80%99s-district-status-restored-notification-issued/|title=Karachi\u2019s district status restored, notification issued|last=Abbasi|first=Saeed|date=2011-07-10|website=The News Tribe|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> and Gulshan Town was re-organized as part of [[District of East Karachi|Karachi East District]] in 2015.\n\n== Location ==\nGulshan Town was bordered by [[Gadap Town]] to the north, the [[Faisal Cantonment|Faisal]] and [[Malir Cantonment|Malir]] Cantonments to the east, [[Jamshed Town]] to the southwest, and [[Gulberg (Karachi)|Gulberg]] and [[Liaquatabad Town|Liaquatabad]] to the west.\n\n== History ==\nThe federal government under [[Pervez Musharraf]], who seized power in a [[1999 Pakistani coup d'\u00e9tat|1999 coup d'etat]], introduced local government reforms in the year 2000, which eliminated the previous \"third tier of government\" ([[Divisions of Pakistan|administrative divisions]]) and replaced it with the fourth tier ([[Districts of Pakistan|districts]]). The effect in Karachi was the dissolution of the former [[Karachi Division]] in 2001, and the merging of its five districts to form a new Karachi City-District with eighteen autonomous constituent towns including Gulshan Town. In 2011,<ref name=\":0\" /> the system was disbanded but remained in place for bureaucratic administration until 2015, when the [[Karachi Metropolitan Corporation]] system was reintroduced. In 2015, Gulshan Town was re-organized as part of [[District of East Karachi|Karachi East]] district.\n\nLate commissioner of Karachi Mr. ([[Syed Darbar Ali Shah]]) envisioned setting up a new town Gulshan e iqbal on April 16, 1966. It was originally KDA scheme 24 which was renamed in the Name of Great poet Allama Muhammad Iqbal. Town saw lot of development after setting up of Civic Center and Expo Center Karachi.\n\n== Demographics ==\nThe population of Gulshan Town was estimated to be about 650,000 at the 1998 census, of which 99% are [[Muslim]]. There are several ethnic groups in Gulshan Town including [[Muhajir (Pakistan)|Muhajirs]], [[Sindhi people|Sindhis]], [[Punjabi people|Punjabis]], [[Kashmiri people|Kashmiris]], [[Saraiki people|Seraikis]], [[Pashtun people|Pakhtuns]], [[Baloch people|Balochis]], etc. The population of Gulshan Town was estimated to be nearly one million before census 2017. A small number of [[Konkani Muslims]] are also settled in the Kokan Cooperative Housing Society of Gulshan-e-Iqbal Town.\n\n== Neighbourhoods ==\n[[File:Safari Park Karachi.jpg|thumb|left|Safari Park]]\nGulshan Town is the location of the main [[University of Karachi]] campus, as well as the offices of the [[City District Government]] of Karachi and the Attorney General of [[Sindh]] province. There are also few large parks which includes [[Aziz Bhatti Park]], Askari Park, Aladin Park and the [[Safari Park (Karachi)|Safari Park]].\n{{columns-list|colwidth=18em|\n* [[Sindh Baloch Cooperative Housing Society]]\n* [[Delhi Mercantile Society]]\n* [[Essa Nagri]]\n* [[Gulshan-e-Iqbal I]]\n* [[Gulshan-e-Iqbal II]]\n* [[Gulzar-e-Hijri]]\n* [[Gulistan-e-Johar]]\n* [[Abbas Town]]\n* [[Kokan Cooperative Housing Society]]\n* [[Jamali Colony]]\n* [[Metroville Colony]]\n* [[Pehlwan Goth]]\n* [[Pir Ilahi Buksh Colony|P.I.B. Colony]]\n* [[Safoora Goth]]\n* [[Shanti Nagar]]\n* [[Sachal Goth]]\n* [[KESC Society]]\n}}\n\n== Education ==\nGulshan-e-Iqbal may be called as a university town having more than a dozen of Higher Education institutions. Few of the major institutions are as follows:\n* University of Karachi\n* NED-UET karachi\n* IBA karachi\n* SSUET\n* Federal Urdu University\n* Usman University\n* Agha Khan University\n* Liaquat National Medical University\n* Indus University\n* Karachi School of Arts\n* Iqra University\n* ICMAP\nand several others\n\n== See also ==\n* Zeenatabad Society \n* [[Sharfabad Society]]\n* [[Bahadurabad]]\n* [[City District Government]]\n* [[Karachi]]\n* [[Lahore]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.karachicity.gov.pk/ Karachi Website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140808225246/http://seccap2014.com/ Sindh E-Centralized College Admission Program]\n* [http://www.dawn.com/wps/wcm/connect/dawn-content-library/dawn/news/media-gallery/04-ofencroachmentsandmegaprojects-qs-01 Karachi: Of encroachments and mega projects]\n* [http://www.dawn.com/wps/wcm/connect/dawn-content-library/dawn/news/pakistan/metropolitan/16-the-issue-of-squatters-on-land-needed-for-new-projects-hs-09 The issue of squatters on land needed for new projects]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160106031137/http://www.hospitalfinder.pk/view/location/gulshan-e-iqbal/ Hospitals In Gulshan Town]\n\n{{Karachi Towns}}\n{{Neighbourhoods of Karachi}}\n{{Karachi}}\n\n{{coord|24|55|N|67|05|E|display=title|type:city_region:PK}}\n\n[[Category:Gulshan Town| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Pakistani English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->| name                            = Gulshan Town\n| native_name                     = <br/>{{Nastaliq|\u06af\u0644\u0634\u0646 \u0679\u0627\u0624\u0646}}\n| settlement_type                 = [[Towns in Karachi|Constituent Town of Karachi]]\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->| image_skyline                   = \n| image_caption                   = Millennium Mall, Askari Chowrangi\n| image_flag                      = \n| image_seal                      = \n| image_map                       = GulshanTown Karachi.PNG\n| map_caption                     = Gulshan Town was divided into 13 Union Councils\n<!-- Location ------------------>| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Pakistan]]\n| subdivision_type1               = Province\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Sindh]]\n| subdivision_type2               = City District\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Karachi]]\n| parts_type                      = Union Councils\n| parts_style                     = para\n| parts                           = 13\n| p1                              = [[Civic Centre (Karachi)|Civic Centre]]\n| p2                              = [[Delhi Mercantile Society]]\n| p3                              = [[Essa Nagri]]\n| p4                              = [[Gillani Railway Station]]\n| p5                              = [[Gulshan-e-Iqbal I]]\n| p6                              = [[Gulshan-e-Iqbal II]]\n| p7                              = [[Gulzar-e-Hijri]]\n| p8                              = [[Jamali Colony]]\n| p9                              = [[Metroville Colony]]\n| p10                             = [[Pehlwan Goth]]\n| p11                             = [[Pir Ilahi Buksh Colony|P.I.B. Colony]]\n| p12                      