 the cast of ''Total Divas''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/2013-08-26/wwe-raw-results-26143822/page-5|title=Raw results: Bryan suffers corporate justice against Orton and The Shield|work=WWE}}</ref> Following this, JoJo appeared at ringside to show support for her ''Total Divas'' co-stars during their matches. JoJo was booked in her first match on ''Raw'' on October 7, teaming with Natalya and [[Eva Marie]] in a winning effort against [[Alicia Fox]], [[Rosa Mendes]], and [[Aksana (wrestler)|Aksana]] in a six diva tag-team match, however she was never tagged into the match.<ref>{{cite web|author=James Caldwell|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wwerawreport/article_73792.shtml|title=Caldwell's WWE Raw Results 10/7 (Hour 1): Battleground PPV fall-out, WWE Title match to continue at next PPV, one \"firing,\" Bruno Sammartino, more|publisher=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=October 7, 2013|accessdate=October 7, 2013}}</ref> The Total Divas defeated The True Divas (Fox, Aksana, Divas Champion AJ, [[Kaitlyn (wrestler)|Kaitlyn]], Mendes, [[Tamina Snuka]] and [[Summer Rae]]) in an [[Professional wrestling tag team match types#Elimination tag team matches|elimination tag-team match]] at the [[Survivor Series (2013)|Survivor Series]] pay-per-view,<ref name=\"SurviorSeries2013\">{{cite web|last=Mike|first=Johnson|title=Complete WWE Survivor Series blog, or... Daniel Bryan is sorely missed in the main event picture|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/81796/ongoing-wwe-survivor-series-blog-pregame-show-thoughts.html|publisher=Pro Wrestling Insider|accessdate=November 24, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Zach|first=Linder|title=Natalya, The Bellas, The Funkadactyls, JoJo & Eva Marie def. Divas Champion AJ Lee, Tamina Snuka, Kaitlyn, Rosa Mendes, Summer Rae, Aksana & Alicia Fox|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/survivorseries/2013/divas-traditional-survivor-series-elimination-match-26164462|publisher=[[WWE]]|accessdate=November 24, 2013}}</ref> and the following night on ''Raw'' in a rematch, where she achieved her first in-ring victory after [[Pin (professional wrestling)|pinning]] and eliminating Tamina Snuka.<ref name=\"SurvivorSeriesRematch\">{{cite web|last=Trionfo|first=Richard|title=Live, ongoing, WWE Raw report: 14 Divas elimination match twice in two days|url=http://www.pwinsider.com/article/81817/live-ongoing-wwe-raw-report-14-divas-elimination-match-twice-in-two-days.html|publisher=Pro Wrestling Insider|accessdate=November 25, 2013}}</ref>\n\n=== Ring announcer (2013\u2013present) ===\n[[File:JoJo NXT Live Event.jpg|thumb|upright|JoJo working as ring announcer during an [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] [[house show]] in March 2015]]\nJoJo later moved to WWE's [[Farm team#Professional wrestling|developmental territory]] [[NXT (WWE brand)|NXT]] in late 2013, after it was confirmed she would not be returning to ''Total Divas'' for its second season. She subsequently became the [[ring announcer]] for ''NXT''. In April 2015, JoJo was promoted to the main roster and began serving as the regular ring announcer on ''[[WWE Main Event|Main Event]]'', ''[[WWE SmackDown|SmackDown]]'', ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]'' and [[pay-per-view]]s as well as a backstage interviewer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/inside/wwe-divas/lilian-garcia-surgery-update-27307266|title=Lilian Garcia undergoes knee surgery|website=[[WWE]]|date=April 17, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/wweppvs/article_85054.shtml|title=CALDWELL'S PAYBACK PPV REPORT 5/17: Ongoing \"virtual-time\" coverage of four-way WWE World Title match, I Quit, more|author=Caldwell, James|website=Pro Wrestling Torch|date=May 17, 2015|accessdate=May 17, 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Other media ==\nOfferman was part of the main cast for the first season of the reality television show ''Total Divas'' produced by WWE and [[E!]]. The show began airing in July 2013.<ref name=\"TD\">{{cite web|url=http://pwtorch.com/artman2/publish/WWE_News_3/article_71912.shtml|title=WWE News: WWE & E! announce \"Total Divas\" details, number of episodes, male cast members|date=July 12, 2013|last=Caldwell|first=James|accessdate=December 22, 2013|publisher=Pro Wrestling Torch}}</ref> Offerman was replaced by [[Summer Rae]] for the second season.<ref>{{cite web|title=New cast member for Total Divas|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/96-wwe/35145-new-cast-member-for-total-divas|work=Wrestling Observer Newsletter|accessdate=January 27, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/wwe-news/46387-new-cast-member-for-new-season-of-total-divas|title=New cast member for new season of 'Total Divas'|date=January 27, 2014|last=Martin|first=Adam|accessdate=February 2, 2014|publisher=WrestleView}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Television ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|2013,<br>2015\u20132018\n|''[[Total Divas]]''\n|Herself\n|Main cast (season 1) <br> Guest (season 3\u20139): 28 episodes\n|-\n|}\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Single\n! Album\n|-\n| 2013\n| \"Somebody Call My Momma\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/wwe-somebody-call-my-momma/id668791970|title=WWE: Somebody Call My Momma \u2013 Single|publisher=[[iTunes Store]]|accessdate=December 27, 2015}}</ref>\n| Non album single\n|}\n\n== Personal life ==\nOfferman is the daughter of former professional [[baseball]] player [[Jos\u00e9 Offerman]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwenxt/nxt-10-count-jojo-27496134|title=NXT 10-Count: JoJo|author=[[Byron Saxton|Saxton, Byron]]|website=[[WWE]]|date=June 11, 2015|accessdate=June 12, 2015}}</ref> She is of [[Mexican people|Mexican]] and [[People of the Dominican Republic|Dominican]] descent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ItsJoseann|title=Joseann Offerman|website=Twitter|accessdate=July 8, 2015}}{{Primary source inline|date=March 2020}}</ref> She is in a relationship with [[WWE]] wrestler [[Bray Wyatt]] and on March 27, 2019, Offerman announced via Instagram that they were expecting,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2828204-wwe-announcer-jojo-announces-pregnancy-with-boyfriend-bray-wyatt|title=WWE Announcer Jojo Announces Pregnancy with Boyfriend Bray Wyatt|last=Daniels|first=Tim|date=March 27, 2019|website=Bleacher Report}}</ref> which was born on May 18, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ewrestlingnews.com/news/bray-wyatt-and-jojo-welcome-their-new-son-to-the-world/amp|title=Bray Wyatt and Jojo welcome their new son to the world}}</ref> WWE Superstar [[Braun Strowman]] is the child's [[Godparent|godfather]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/wwe/news/14203/11782833/braun-strowman-bray-wyatt-is-a-unique-talent-and-id-love-to-work-with-him |title=Bray Wyatt is a unique talent and I'd Love to Work with Him |last=Lake |first=Jefferson |date=August 11, 2019 |website=[[Sky Sports]]}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and accomplishments ==\n* '''''[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]'''''\n** [[List of Wrestling Observer Newsletter awards#Worst Worked Match of the Year|Worst Worked Match of the Year]] (2013) \u2013 with [[Brie Bella]], [[Cameron (wrestler)|Cameron]], [[Eva Marie]], [[Naomi (wrestler)|Naomi]], [[Natalya Neidhart|Natalya]], and [[Nikki Bella]] vs. [[AJ Lee]], [[Aksana (wrestler)|Aksana]], [[Alicia Fox]], [[Kaitlyn (wrestler)|Kaitlyn]], [[Rosa Mendes]], [[Summer Rae]], and [[Tamina Snuka]] at [[Survivor Series (2013)|Survivor Series]]<ref name=\"WON13\">{{cite journal|last=Meltzer|first=Dave|authorlink=Dave Meltzer|date=January 27, 2014|title=Jan 27 2014 Wrestling Observer Newsletter: 2013 Annual awards issue, best in the world in numerous categories, plus all the news in pro-wrestling and MMA over the past week and more|journal=Wrestling Observer Newsletter|location=Campbell, California|issn=1083-9593|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/component/content/article/110-wrestling-observer-newsletter/35067-jan-27-2014-wrestling-observer-newsletter-2013-annual-awards-issue-best-in-the-world-in-numerous-categories-plus-all-the-news-in-pro-wrestling-and-mma-over-the-past-week-and-more|page=32}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|JoJo Offerman}}\n* {{WWE superstar|jojo|JoJo}}\n* {{Twitter|name=Joseann Offerman}}\n* {{IMDb name|nm5801121|Joseann Offerman}}\n{{WWE personnel}}\n{{Total Divas}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Offerman, JoJo}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:American people of Dominican Republic descent]]\n[[Category:American female professional wrestlers]]\n[[Category:American professional wrestlers of Mexican descent]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestling announcers]]\n[[Category:Professional wrestling managers and valets]]\n[[Category:People from Toluca Lake, Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n", "name_user": "NotTheFakeJTP", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed parameter", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JoJo_Offerman"}
